											"content": [
												{
													"nodeType": "text",
													"data": {
														"target": null,
														"uri": null
													},
													"value": "While DNS firewalls protect DNS servers only, network firewalls guard the boundaries of the network itself. By monitoring and controlling incoming and outgoing traffic based on set security rules, they filter data packets and prevent unauthorized access. Advanced features of network firewalls also block sophisticated cyber-attacks and ensure compliance with security policies.",
